summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous resolutions on international terrorism and its threat to Afghanistan, reaffirms its commitment to the country's sovereignty, independence, territorial integrity, and national unity. The Council expresses concern over the security situation in Afghanistan, citing ongoing violent and terrorist activities by the Taliban, Al-Qaida, ISIL, and their affiliates. It supports a peaceful, stable, and prosperous Afghanistan and urges an immediate reduction in violence leading to a ceasefire to facilitate peace negotiations.

The Council reiterates its support for the fight against illicit production and trafficking of drugs from Afghanistan and recognizes the threats posed by the Taliban, illegal armed groups, and criminals involved in narcotics trade and illicit exploitation of natural resources.

Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter, the Council:

1. Decides that all States shall continue measures required by resolution 2255 regarding individuals and entities designated as the Taliban or associated with it;
2. Extends the mandate of the 1267/1988 Analytical Support and Sanctions Monitoring Team for 12 months to support the Committee;
3. Directs the Monitoring Team to gather information on non-compliance, facilitate assistance on capacity-building, and provide recommendations to the Committee;
4. Decides to actively review the implementation of the measures outlined and consider adjustments as necessary;
5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
The Monitoring Team shall operate under the direction of the Committee and have the following responsibilities:

(a) Submit an annual comprehensive report to the Committee on implementation of measures by Member States;

(b) Assist the Committee in reviewing names on the List, including through travel and contact with Member States;

(c) Follow up on requests to Member States for information on implementation of measures;

(d) Submit a comprehensive programme of work to the Committee for review and approval;

(e) Gather information on non-compliance with measures and provide recommendations;

(f) Present recommendations to assist Member States with implementation of measures;

(g) Assist the Committee in considering proposals for listing;

(h) Bring to the Committee's attention new or noteworthy circumstances for delisting;

(i) Consult with Member States before travel to selected Member States;

(j) Encourage Member States to submit names and identifying information for inclusion on the List;

(k) Consult with the Committee, Government of Afghanistan, or relevant Member States on listing and delisting;

(l) Present additional identifying information to assist the Committee in keeping the List updated;

(m) Collate, assess, monitor and report on implementation of measures;

(n) Consult with Member States, UNAMA, and other UN agencies;

(o) Cooperate with UNODC and engage in dialogue with Member States and organizations on narcotics trafficking;

(p) Provide an update to the special report of the Monitoring Team;

(q) Consult with Member States' intelligence and security services;

(r) Consult with private sector representatives on practical implementation of the assets freeze;

(s) Cooperate with ISIL and Al-Qaida Sanctions Committee and other counter-terrorism bodies;

(t) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and international organizations on asset freezing;

(u) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and international organizations on travel ban and assets freeze;

(v) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and international organizations on the threat posed by improvised explosive devices (IEDs).
The Monitoring Team shall: 

(w) Work with international and regional organizations to promote awareness of and compliance with the measures;

(x) Cooperate with INTERPOL and Member States to obtain and exchange information on listed individuals, including biometric and biographic data;

(y) Assist other subsidiary bodies of the Security Council and their expert panels in enhancing cooperation with INTERPOL;

(z) Assist the Committee in facilitating capacity-building assistance to Member States;

(aa) Report to the Committee on a regular basis or as requested on its work, including visits and activities;

(bb) Study and report on the threat posed by individuals, groups, and entities associated with the Taliban and recommend measures to confront it;

(cc) Gather information on travel exemptions and report to the Committee as appropriate;

(dd) Undertake any other responsibility identified by the Committee.
